arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XI: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
0.9 m north south -by- 3.0 m east west.

Locus 6 consists of the wash and soil within the "bathroom." For the most part the soil in the room is undifferentiated and the stratigraphy is less complex than in the adjoining "hypocaust room." This locus fills the main part of the bathroom and covers/abuts the soil loci which denote the soil in the niches of the bathroom (loci 10, 11, 12, 13). The Munsell color of the soil in this locus is 7.5yr 5/4, brown. There is a large amount of plaster and pottery in this layer of all sizes and the consistency of the soil is fine silt.
